
### tree renders siblings, nesting, and the orphan
$ git stack tree
* main (trunk)
    feat-a (needs restack: 1 behind)
      feat-b (1 commit(s))
        feat-b1 (1 commit(s))
      feat-c (1 commit(s))
    feat-x-child (parent 'feat-x' missing; run `git stack sync`)
[exit 0]

### parent reports the recorded parent
$ git stack parent
feat-a
[exit 0]

### restack replays the sibling subtrees onto an advanced parent
$ git stack tree
  main (trunk)
    feat-a (needs restack: 1 behind)
    * feat-b (needs restack: 1 behind)
        feat-b1 (1 commit(s))
      feat-c (needs restack: 1 behind)
    feat-x-child (parent 'feat-x' missing; run `git stack sync`)
[exit 0]
$ git stack restack
restacking stack rooted at feat-a
restacking feat-a onto main
restacking feat-b onto feat-a
restacking feat-b1 onto feat-b
restacking feat-c onto feat-a
done.
[exit 0]
$ git stack tree
  main (trunk)
    feat-a (2 commit(s))
    * feat-b (1 commit(s))
        feat-b1 (1 commit(s))
      feat-c (1 commit(s))
    feat-x-child (parent 'feat-x' missing; run `git stack sync`)
[exit 0]

### sync heals the orphan onto the trunk
$ git stack sync
syncing stack rooted at feat-x-child
'feat-x-child': parent 'feat-x' no longer exists; reparenting onto trunk 'main'
done.
[exit 0]
$ git stack tree
  main (trunk)
    feat-a (2 commit(s))
      feat-b (1 commit(s))
        feat-b1 (1 commit(s))
      feat-c (1 commit(s))
  * feat-x-child (1 commit(s))
[exit 0]
feat-x-child parent: main

### sync recovers a branch whose parent was squash-merged and deleted
$ git stack sync
syncing stack rooted at feature-b
'feature-b': parent 'feature-a' no longer exists; reparenting onto trunk 'main'
restacking feature-b onto main
done.
[exit 0]
feature-b parent: main
feature-b behind main: 0
feature-b commits above main: 1
feature-b stackBase == main tip: yes

### a stack past the 4 KB scan boundary renders and syncs intact
branch-list scan exceeds the 4 KB backtick cap: yes
stack-config scan exceeds the 4 KB backtick cap: yes
$ git stack tree | grep zzz
    zzz-stack-bottom 
      zzz-stack-top 
[exit 0]
zzz rows in tree (expect 2): 2
$ git stack sync
syncing stack rooted at zzz-stack-bottom
done.
[exit 0]
zzz-stack-top parent after sync: zzz-stack-bottom
zzz-stack-bottom parent after sync: main

### an orphan-looking stack past the branch-list cap is not 'healed' away
branch-list scan exceeds the 4 KB backtick cap: yes
stack-config scan (small and accurate here): branch.zzz-stack-bottom.stackparent mainbranch.zzz-stack-top.stackparent zzz-stack-bottom
$ git stack tree | grep zzz
    zzz-stack-bottom 
      zzz-stack-top 
[exit 0]
zzz rows in tree (expect 2): 2
$ git stack sync
syncing stack rooted at zzz-stack-bottom
done.
[exit 0]
zzz-stack-top parent after sync: zzz-stack-bottom
